featured_reviews.review_id:
From the moment I stepped inside, I was welcomed with warmth and kindness by the members of the community. The mosque's architecture and design exuded a sense of serenity and beauty, creating a peaceful ambiance that instantly put me at ease.

The prayers and sermons led by the Imam were profound and heartfelt, touching the hearts of everyone present. The devotion and sincerity displayed by the worshippers during congregational prayers left a lasting impression on me, fostering a sense of unity and belonging.

What struck me the most was the atmosphere of inclusivity and acceptance at the mosque. Regardless of one's background or beliefs, everyone was treated with respect and kindness, emphasizing the true essence of Islam - love, compassion, and harmony.

featured_reviews.review_id:
It's located in Mumbai, off Muhammad Ali Road
Walkable distance to Minara Masjid, Pydhonie, Bhendi Bazaar
It's the Markaz (for Mumbai South) of Da'awat-o-Tabligh connected to Markaz Nizamuddin in Delhi considered as Center of the World of Da'awat-o-Tabligh
Here jama'ats come & go all over India and World
Masjid in Arabic/Urdu (Mosque in English) is a place of Worship in Islaam
Devotees offer/perform 5 times prayers everyday (namely Fajr, Dhuhr, A'sr, Maghrib, E'shaa)
Also, Juma' prayer, Eid Prayers, all prayers are performed in congregation
This is Hanafi Masjid (Hanafi school of thoughts) one of the four schools of thoughts (namely Hanafi, Shafai', Hambali, Maliki)
Masjid is managed by Trust
Trustees are also committed towards the overall management of Trust
Masjid's cleanliness/hygiene of the place is optimum, giving the in coming crowd an extremely nice experience of worshiping.
Other development works are required, need more space for Toilets

featured_reviews.review_id:
Minara Masjid stands as a majestic landmark in the heart of Muhammad Ali Road, Mumbai. The green domes and ancient architectural marvel draw attention to its significance. The intricate Islamic art on windows and doors, coupled with the white marble Mimber, add to its beauty.

The history of Minara Masjid is enriched with two compelling stories. One narrates the tale of Islamic scholars and saints who migrated from Arabia to Mumbai, intending to build a mosque for prayers. With dedication and companionship, they constructed this mosque in a matter of months, and today it proudly stands as the crown of Mumbai's Muhammad Ali Road.

Another story unfolds within the mosque, suggesting that the awliya Allah, who were merchants and scholars, ordered jinns to build the mosque for them. The mosque, completed in a remarkably short time, showcases breathtaking Islamic art, a testament to the divine presence within its walls.

Inside Minara Masjid, two revered dargahs of unknown and known saints from Arabia can be found. These migrants, who were both merchants and Islamic scholars, left an indelible mark on the mosque and its surroundings. The Noor, or divine light, that emanates from the mosque's domes and structures is truly exceptional.

A visit to Minara Masjid is a journey through history and spirituality, where the artistry and stories intertwine, creating an atmosphere that is both awe-inspiring and tranquil.
